{"ID":270312, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"312\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs311.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs313.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 312<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">Peter<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> and Stephen testify<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> that they saw the Son of Man standing on the right hand of God.<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span>\n  Any person that had seen the heavens opened<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> knows that there are three personages in the heavens\n  who hold the keys of power, and one presides over all.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">If any man attempts to refute<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> what I am about to say, after I have made it plain, let him\n  beware.<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">The Son Does What the Father Did<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">As the Father hath power in Himself, so hath the Son power in Himself,<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> to lay down His life\n  and take it again,<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> so He has a body of His own. The Son doeth what He hath seen the Father do:<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span>\n  then the Father hath some day laid down His life and taken it again;<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> so He has a body of His own;<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span>\n  each one will be in His own body; and yet the sectarian world believe the body of the Son is\n  identical with the Father&rsquo;s.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Gods have an ascendency over the angels, who are ministering servants.<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> In the resurrection,\n  some are raised to be angels, others are raised to become Gods.<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">These things are revealed in the most holy places in a Temple<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> prepared for that purpose. Many\n  of the sects cry out, &ldquo;Oh, I have the testimony of Jesus; I have the spirit of God; but away with Joe\n  Smith; he says he is a prophet; but there are to be no prophets or revelators in the last days.&rdquo; Stop,\n  sir! The Revelator says that the testimony of Jesus is the spirit of prophecy;<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> so by your own mouth\n  you are condemned.<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> But to the text. Why gather the people together in this place? For the same\n  purpose that Jesus wanted to gather the Jews<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span>&mdash;to receive the ordinances, the blessings, and glories\n  that God has in store for His Saints.<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">I will now ask this assembly and all the Saints if you will now build this house<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> and receive the\n  ordinances and blessings which God has in store for you;<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> or will you not build unto the Lord this\n  house, and let Him pass by and bestow these blessings<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> upon another people?<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span> I pause for a reply.\n  (June 11, 1843.) DHC 5:423-427.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">The Cause of the Prophet&rsquo;s Success&mdash;Love for His Fellow-Man<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">Joseph remarked that all was well between him and the heavens;<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span> that he had no enmity against\n  any one;<span class=\"footRef\">24<\/span> and as the prayer of Jesus, or his pattern, so prayed Joseph&mdash;Father, for-<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108092\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108092)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108092)\">Matt. 17:5<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110524\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110524)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110524)\">2 Pet. 1:16-17<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109027\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109027)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109027)\">Acts 7:55-56<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114405\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114405)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114405)\">D&amp;C 76:20-23<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"117101\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 117101)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(117101)\">JS&mdash;H 1:17<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107442\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107442)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107442)\">Ezek. 1:1<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107793\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107793)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107793)\">Matt. 3:16<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108633\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108633)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108633)\">John 1:51<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110897\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110897)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110897)\">1 Ne. 1:8<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112448\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112448)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112448)\">Hel. 5:48<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112636\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112636)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112636)\">3 Ne. 17:24<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112715\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112715)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112715)\">3 Ne. 28:13<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115437\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115437)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115437)\">D&amp;C 107:19<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116605\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116605)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116605)\">D&amp;C 137:1<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116865\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116865)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116865)\">Moses 7:3<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109505\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109505)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109505)\">1 Cor. 11:16<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109575\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109575)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109575)\">1 Cor. 14:37<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109714\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109714)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109714)\">Gal. 1:9<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109906\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109906)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109906)\">Col. 2:4,8<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109977\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109977)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109977)\">2 Thes. 3:14<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110027\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110027)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110027)\">1 Tim. 6:3-5<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106374\"><a href=\"javascri